"{\"abstract\":\"We propose a least-squares formulation to the noisy hand-eye calibration problem using dual-quaternions, and introduce efficient algorithms to find the exact optimal solution, based on analytic properties of the problem, avoiding non-linear optimization. We further present simple analytic approximate solutions which provide remarkably good estimations compared to the exact solution. In addition, we show how to generalize our solution to account for a given extrinsic prior in the cost function. To the best of our knowledge our algorithm is the most efficient approach to optimally solve the hand-eye calibration problem.\",\"arxivId\":\"2002.10838\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"121783979\",\"name\":\"A. Dekel\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/121783979\"},{\"authorId\":\"1411379030\",\"name\":\"Linus H\\u00e4renstam-Nielsen\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1411379030\"},{\"authorId\":\"3086456\",\"name\":\"S. Caccamo\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3086456\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3053836\",\"name\":\"Hyuncheol Kim\"},{\"authorId\":\"3112477\",\"name\":\"Taeyong Kuc\"},{\"authorId\":\"2595744\",\"name\":\"K. Lee\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/ICCE-Asia49877.2020.9277421\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"92e7748564a83638a4ecc0d97a906cc64879923e\",\"title\":\"Hand-eye Calibration using Images Restored by Deep Learning\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/92e7748564a83638a4ecc0d97a906cc64879923e\",\"venue\":\"2020 IEEE International Conference on Consumer Electronics - Asia (ICCE-Asia)\",\"year\":2020}],\"corpusId\":211296815,\"doi\":\"10.1109/cvpr42600.2020.01361\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":true,\"is_publisher_licensed\":true,\"paperId\":\"ae1c2fa5a58c3d1e6a04269c8c139448ec85d530\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2194189